Bush's energy plan.=20
My, how the scene has changed. In mid-May President Bush unveiled a=20
Cheney-authored energy plan that promoted drilling and nuking and mining but=
=20
overlooked conserving. That's when the vice president dismissed conservation=
=20
as a "personal virtue" but no energy policy.=20
The 170-page Bush policy did speak ominously of a growing "energy crisis."=20
At the time, gasoline seemed headed to $3 a gallon. Rolling blackouts=20
interrupted California's power. Winter natural gas prices had spiked.=20
Bush seemed confident he could push his energy policy through a House and=20
Senate dominated by Republicans.=20
